<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-28T14:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-27T06:07:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.51/621: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-06-28T14:15:00-05:00" notBefore="1919-06-27T16:00:00+04:53"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 28, 1919, 2:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at]
                            Omsk.</p>
                        <p>“288. June 27, 4 p.m. Referring to Department’s June 23, 2 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d410fn13">Not printed.</note> For financial and
                            political reasons Omsk Government desires American Government loan:
                            $325,000,000 desired, $125,000,000 to cancel earlier loans made in
                            United States and $200,000,000 for establishing credit wherewith to
                            facilitate purchase of commercial commodities in the United States.
                                <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”<note n="14" xml:id="d410fn14">Notation on telegram: “Conferred with <persName corresp="#p_US1">Ughet</persName> and explained no loans to
                                unrecognized government. 7/14 B[reckinridge] L[ong].”</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>